    • load

      public String load(String firstToken) throws IOException, MMIOException, ProofAsstException
      Default load method for ProofWorkStmt that does not validate the input.

      This is used for GeneratedProofStmt and CommentStmt -- and any other possible future statement where you, theoretically, want to be able to parse and load the input statement but don't care about the contents.

      Output/Updates

      • accum tokens and whitespace into stmtText, but don't validate the contents, just look for the start of the next statement.
      • return nextToken after trailing whitespace, the start of the next statement.
      Parameters:
      firstToken - the first token
      Returns:
      the nextToken
      Throws:
      IOException - if IO error
      MMIOException - if an error occurred
      ProofAsstException - if an error occurred

    • loadStmtTextGetRequiredToken

      protected String loadStmtTextGetRequiredToken(String prevToken) throws IOException, MMIOException, ProofAsstException
      Loads input token into ProofWorkStmt's stmtText then loads following whitespace and returns the next token, but without loading it into stmtText.

      Blows up if there is no next token or whitespace because they are required at the current parse position within the ProofWorkStmt.

      Parameters:
      prevToken - the first token of the Stmt
      Returns:
      the nextToken
      Throws:
      IOException - if an error occurred
      MMIOException - if an error occurred
      ProofAsstException - if an error occurred

    • loadStmtTextGetOptionalToken

      protected String loadStmtTextGetOptionalToken(String prevToken) throws IOException, MMIOException, ProofAsstException
      Loads input token into ProofWorkStmt's stmtText then loads following whitespace and returns the *next* token, but without loading it into stmtText.

      Returns empty String (length = 0) if end of file reached.

      the next token

    • loadStmtTextGetNextStmt

      protected String loadStmtTextGetNextStmt(String prevToken) throws IOException, MMIOException, ProofAsstException
      Loads input token into ProofWorkStmt's stmtText then loads following whitespace and returns the next token, but without loading it into stmtText.

      Blows up if the next token does not begin in column 1, which indicates the start of the next statement.

      Returns empty String (length = 0) if end of file reached.

      Parameters:
      prevToken - the first token
      Returns:
      the next token
      Throws:
      IOException - if an error occurred
      MMIOException - if an error occurred
      ProofAsstException - if an error occurred

    • loadAllStmtTextGetNextStmt

      protected String loadAllStmtTextGetNextStmt(String prevToken) throws IOException, MMIOException, ProofAsstException
      Loads input token into ProofWorkStmt's stmtText then loads ALL following whitespace AND tokens until the start of the next statement, returning the next token without loading it into

      Returns empty String (length = 0) if end of file reached.

      Parameters:

      Returns:
